  "body": "As far a I understand it is consider an EIP20-compliance to add custom functions that isn't listed in the EIP20 interface?\r\n\r\nThe [EIP20 page](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-20.md) listing some optional functions - so it's looks like we're restricted only to those optional functions above the six mandatory functions but not any other (otherwise why to write it down as optional - any other function is optional)?\r\n\r\nSo my suggestion is to:\r\n1. delete those optional function or to change the term to \"nice to have\" or something else.\r\n2. may be also add some clarification that the functions is the minimum required and it's possible to add custom functions.",
