    "body": "Great reference.\r\nThanks.\r\nBut if we'll get into nuances so it is still not smooth.\r\nIn one Hand the EIP20 use the term \"OPTIONAL\" but in the other hand it says that \"interfaces and other contracts MUST NOT expect these values to be present\" - so it's moving out all the meaning of \"OPTIONAL\" according to the definition in the reference that said that we should expect to it.\r\n\r\nMaybe the term SHOULD\\RECOMMENDED it more accurate.",
